{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπονείδιστος</b>, ον, <br /> <b>to be reproached, disgraceful, shameful,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 689; ἐ. εἰρήνη 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.106 (_comparative_),compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.336; ἀμαθία 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 29b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τινι to one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 8.34 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπονείδιστόν ἐστι παρά τισι is <b>matter of reproach,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 26.19 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὄνομα τοὐπονείδιστον βροτοῖς the name <b>of reproach</b> among men, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 922 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1119a25 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 8.19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-τως</b> <b>shamefully,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 633e, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.60 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in <i>active</i> sense, <b>so as to shame,</b> ψέγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.14.5. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7480","accentedUnicode":"ἐπονείδιστος","shortDef":"reviled","mediumDef":"reviled","stepGloss":"reviled","stepTransliteration":"eponeidistos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}